name: The Lausanne Métro Tragedy
description: This footage was filmed back in 2014 during my visit to a film festival in Lausanne before i got cornered by local polices. It was my last day in town, i decided to take a walk around the lake. As i was walking to get back to the festival venue, the brokeass-cheapskate me took a 'shortcut' by entering the Lausanne Métro with no tickets. I was filming the front view of the train with my blackmagic pocket cinema camera when those muscular polices caught me without any tickets. I got fined 150 CHF for not paying around 3-4 CHF lol. I learned the lesson the hard way.
